  {
    "client_msg_id": "46cba243-0d6f-4fd0-810c-2fa8574276c0",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "The protocol only defines how a block and an app should communicate, which includes requiring blocks to declare an expected schema. But it doesn’t control whether an app like Notion then translates those schemas into something accessible on the open web like JSON-LD or RDF.\n\nThe block schemas would make that translation much easier, but the BP itself can’t govern what individual apps choose to do. It only tries to make it easier for them to create and publish structured data through blocks. We’re trying to walk the line between trying encourage block-based apps to lean into structured data (and give them better tools to implement it) but we can’t govern whether they actually take the extra step and semantically mark-up their publishable pages with something like JSON-LD and/or RDF",
    "user": "U0275EZH3UN",
    "ts": "1654293458.915769",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
